---
title: Command Prompt Compilation and Execution
---
# Using the Command Prompt

Java files can be compiled and ran straight from the command prompt (or terminal on a Mac.)  
First, Java will need to be downloaded and the path must be set. 
Then, To run your program:

- open the command prompt
- navigate to the directory containing your file (cd JavaFiles)
- compile the program (javac HelloWorld.java)
- execute the program (java HelloWorld)
